<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Kobresia</i> <i>myosuroides</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Carex</i> <i>scirpoidea</i> ssp. <i>pseudoscirpoidea</i>, <i>Eleocharis</i> <i>quinqueflora</i>, <i>Gentianopsis</i> <i>holopetala</i>, <i>Juncus</i> <i>arcticus</i>, <i>Perideridia</i> <i>parishii</i>, <i>Thalictrum</i> <i>alpinum</i> and <i>Trichophorum</i> <i>pumilum</i>. Emergent shrubs may be present at low cover, including <i>Arctostaphylos</i> <i>uva</i>-<i>ursi</i> or <i>Salix</i> <i>brachycarpa</i> var. <i>brachycarpa</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 50 cm; cover is continuous. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
